    {
      "id": "05b6f436_931b6503",
      "file_path": ".github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 113,
      "message": "I have some questions on this, we need to pass the jjbini file which in this case it should be stored in GH right? or how are we going to reference config files?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 481,
        "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "jwagantall"
      },
      "updated": "2023-05-01 23:56:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f7786f5d_faa6fe75",
      "file_path": ".github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 113,
      "message": "We can use a generic jjbini file that has just the following section in it:\n\nI would add the following on the lines preceding the jjb test call.\n\n---%<---\nmkdir -p \"${HOME}/.config/jenkins_jobs\"\ncat << EOF > \"${HOME}/.config/jenkins_jobs/jenkins_jobs.ini\"\n[job_builder]\nignore_cache=True\nkeep_descriptions=False\ninclude_path=.\nrecursive=True\nquery_plugins_info=False\nconfig-xml=True\nEOF\n---%<---\n\nWith the above config file you can drop the --recursive and --config-xml parameters.  I'll note that the -o archives/job-configs isn't all that useful as we don't get access to the generated files after the job completes. That being said, not having it is going to spam the console IIRC so whatever.\n\nSetting query_plugins_info to False tells JJB to not talk to any jenkins server at all and find out what version of plugins may be installed. As such it just assumes that latest version of the needed plugin.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1,
        "name": "Andrew Grimberg",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "agrimberg@linuxfoundation.org",
        "username": "agrimberg"
      },
      "updated": "2023-05-02 16:15:46.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "05b6f436_931b6503",
      "unresolved": true
    },
